<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= title %></title>
    <style>
        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
        body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; padding: 20px; background: #f5f5f5; }
        
        header { background: #2c3e50; color: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; margin-bottom: 30px; }
        nav ul { list-style: none; display: flex; gap: 15px; margin-top: 20px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
        nav a { color: #3498db; text-decoration: none; padding: 8px 12px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); border-radius: 5px; }
        
        .management-container {
            background: white;
            padding: 40px;
            border-radius: 15px;
            box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        
        .management-header {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 40px;
            color: #2c3e50;
        }
        
        .management-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
            gap: 30px;
        }
        
        .management-card {
            background: #f8f9fa;
            padding: 30px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            border: 2px solid #3498db;
            text-align: center;
        }
        
        .management-icon {
            font-size: 48px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            color: #3498db;
        }
        
        .btn {
            display: inline-block;
            padding: 12px 30px;
            background: #3498db;
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin-top: 15px;
        }
        
        footer {
            background: #2c3e50;
            color: white;
            padding: 30px;
            text-align: center;
            border-radius: 10px;
            margin-top: 50px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>CSE Motors</h1>
        <nav>
            <%- nav %>
        </nav>
    </header>
    
    <div class="management-container">
        <div class="management-header">
            <h1>üìä Inventory Management</h1>
            <p>Manage vehicle inventory, classifications, and data</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="management-grid">
            <div class="management-card">
                <div class="management-icon">üöó</div>
                <h3>Vehicle Management</h3>
                <p>Add, edit, or remove vehicles from inventory</p>
                <a href="#" class="btn">Manage Vehicles</a>
            </div>
            
            <div class="management-card">
                <div class="management-icon">üè∑Ô∏è</div>
                <h3>Classification Management</h3>
                <p>Manage vehicle classifications (Sports, SUVs, etc.)</p>
                <a href="#" class="btn">Manage Classifications</a>
            </div>
            
            <div class="management-card">
                <div class="management-icon">üìà</div>
                <h3>Inventory Reports</h3>
                <p>View inventory statistics and reports</p>
                <a href="#" class="btn">View Reports</a>
            </div>
            
            <div class="management-card">
                <div class="management-icon">‚öôÔ∏è</div>
                <h3>System Settings</h3>
                <p>Configure inventory system settings</p>
                <a href="#" class="btn">Settings</a>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div style="margin-top: 40px; padding: 25px; background: #e8f4fc; border-radius: 10px;">
            <h3>CSE340 Assignment 3 - Inventory Management System</h3>
            <p>This inventory management page demonstrates the backend capabilities for:</p>
            <ul style="text-align: left; margin: 15px 0; padding-left: 20px;">
                <li>Vehicle inventory tracking</li>
                <li>Classification management</li>
                <li>Database operations (CRUD)</li>
                <li>User authentication (for future development)</li>
                <li>Data validation and error handling</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2025 CSE Motors - CSE340 Assignment 3</p>
        <p><a href="/trigger-error" style="color: #e74c3c;">[Test 500 Error - Assignment 3 Requirement]</a></p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>